Package org.swerverobotics.library.interfaces

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    I2cDeviceSynchUser
    I2cDeviceSynchUser allows one to retrieve an underlying I2cDeviceSynch from an a client of the latter.
    IAccelerationIntegrator
    IAccelerationIntegrator encapsulates an algorithm for integrating acceleration information over time to produce velocity and position.
    IBNO055IMU
    Interface API to the Adafruit 9-DOF Absolute Orientation IMU Fusion Breakout - BNO055 sensor.
    IFunc<TResult>
    IFunc<TResult> represents a nullary function that returns a value of the indicated type.
    IHardwareWrapper<T>
    Advanced: IHardwareWrapper can be used on hardware objects which wrap other, similar hardware objects in order to retrieve the object that they wrapp
    II2cDeviceClient Deprecated
    Code that previously used II2cDeviceClient should use I2cDeviceSynch instead.
    II2cDeviceClientUser Deprecated
    Code that previously used II2cDeviceClientUser should use I2cDeviceSynchUser instead.
    IInterruptableFunc<TResult>
    A variation of IFunc that permits the throwing of an InterruptedException
    IInterruptableRunnable
    A variation on Runnable that allows InterruptedExceptions to be thrown
    IOpModeLoopCounter
    Public interface to the little OpModeLoopCounter utility
    IOpModeManager
    IOpModeManager instances are used as part of a decentralized OpMode registration mechanism.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Acceleration
    Acceleration represents a directed acceleration in three-space.
    AngularVelocity
    AngularVelocity represents a rotation rate in three-space.
    EulerAngles
    Instances of EulerAngles represent a direction in three-dimensional space by way of rotations.
    IBNO055IMU.Parameters
    Instances of Parameters contain data indicating how a BNO055 absolute orientation sensor is to be initialized.
    MagneticFlux
    Instances of MagneticFlux represent a three-dimensional magnetic strength vector.
    NavUtil
    NavUtil is a collection of utilities that provide useful manipulations of objects related to navigation.
    Position
    Position represents a coordinate position in three-space.
    Quaternion
    A Quaternion can indicate an orientation in three-space without the trouble of possible gimbal-lock.
    Velocity
    Velocity represents a directed velocity in three-space.

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Autonomous
    Provides an easy and non-centralized way of determining the OpMode list shown on an FTC Driver Station.
    Disabled
    Provides a way to temporarily disable an OpMode annotated with Autonomous or TeleOp from showing up on the driver station OpMode list.
    OnRobotRunning
    OnRobotRunning annotations can be placed on public static methods which are to be invoked when the robot object in the robot controller application reaches the running state after an initial boot or a 'robot restart'.
    OnRobotStartupFailure
    OnRobotStartupFailure annotations can be placed on public static methods which are to be invoked when the robot object in the robot controller application fails as it is starting up.
    OpModeRegistrar
    Provides an easy and non-centralized way of contributing to the OpMode list shown on an FTC Driver Station.
    TeleOp
    Provides an easy and non-centralized way of determining the OpMode list shown on an FTC Driver Station.
